TRICKY 1 — Circular imports
  Solution: Topological sort (Kahn's algorithm)
  If cycle detected → warn user
  Show EXACTLY which modules cause it
  Suggest fix

TRICKY 2 — __init__.py content
  NOT just "import *"
  That's sloppy and breaks things.
  Instead:
    from .process import process
    from .validate import validate
    from .RoomEngine import RoomEngine
  Explicit. Clean. Sovereign.

TRICKY 3 — Name conflicts between rooms
  room-2 has validate()
  room-3 also has validate()
  Solution: namespace by room
    from .room_2 import validate as room2_validate
    from .room_3 import validate as room3_validate

TRICKY 4 — C++ + Python in same room
  They wire differently.
  Python → __init__.py
  C++    → CMakeLists.txt
  Both   → mesh_manifest.json

TRICKY 5 — Room name sanitization
  "room-2" is not valid Python.
  Must become "room_2"
  But the directory stays "room-2"
  __init__.py handles the alias
